<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="ie=edge" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="./css/styles.css">
  <link rel="icon" href="/img/weather.png">
  <title>About</title>
</head>

<body>
  <div class="main-content">
    {{>header}}
    <h4>{{message}}</h4>
    <p>
      Add the name of a city or place in the search bar and the app will provide you with the weather in that location. If you are looking for an specific place, provide more search terms: <strong>Los Angeles Chile</strong>, is more specific if you are looking for that location, because otherwise the app will go for the most asked for place, and in the case of Los Angeles, that is <strong>Los Angeles, California</strong>. Sorry Chile!
    </p>
    <p>
      Check the repo <a href="https://github.com/Ceheiss/nodejs-weather-app">here</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
  {{>footer}}
</body>

</html>